A trainwreck with Star Wars skin. It was a total cringe from start to finish and obviously a totally rushed production. It lacked originality good storyline and decent plot. I felt embarrassed as a Star Wars fan. Thank god we have the mandalorian

I was 8 years old when the first Star Wars movie was released. Growing up with Star Wars expanded my imagination and I feel like I grew up with this story. A couple of these later Star Wars movies didn't do a lot for me and characters like Jar Jar Binks were a little silly, but I do not understand the critics on this last installment of Star Wars and The Rise of Skywalker. This was a very entertaining movie and my son and I left the movie satisfied with the closure on this story. I think it is an impossible job to satisfy everyone but for the normal Star Wars person in their 50's I was happy and enjoyed the movie. I was entertained, it brought back several old scenes and references to prior films especially those first 3 released. I say 5 Stars. Glad we can all have opinions but why is mine always so different from the critics? If I go to the movies they recommend I am usually falling asleep or find the stories predictable or silly. So if you like the critics in general then ignore my review. However, if you often find the critics to be off base then I hope my review will encourage you go to this movie and just enjoy yourself and have some of those old Star Wars feelings one last time.
Everything happened too fast. It could have been two movies.

Great movie and great way to end the saga! This movie took risks and answered questions all while keeping things interesting. The heartfelt moments made me tear up and I found myself laughing and smiling throughout. Felt like a kid again

For the very first time, I have to agree with critics. This is a mess. No payoff at all. To nothing. Pointless movie to the pointless trilogy. Stuff makes no sense. And the revelation? Boring. It could have been so much more. The resolution to the inner conflicts of the main force-user leads is nothing. Do yourself a favor and don't go, you won't miss anything.

Absolute blast of a film. Performances were great, music amazing, visuals were stunning. Story had great moments, but also a few hiccups and somewhat convenient plot points occasionally.

Overall a satisfying ending to the Saga. While I understand the critics as the film is sloppy and rushed, that's mostly caused by the film prior that they loved so much.

It's not a perfect "film", but it's great Star Wars, and that's all I needed to end this Saga happy.
Absolutely amazing film! Great way to end the SkyWalker Saga!! If you love Star Wars, you definitely gotta watch the film!

This was such a great movie. It had me laughing and crying and sometimes both at the same time.  JJ Abrams once again shows he knows what Star Wars is and this was a perfect ending to the Skywalker Saga.

Overall I thought is was rather anticlimactic. Not much creativity. It seemed like Abrams struggled to come up with an idea, and then just threw some stuff together. Not a good ending to the saga. The last scene with Rey and Kylo was a bit ridiculous. However, it is a Star Wars film so it is a must see.
